==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: handled
<hw>handled</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>fitted with or having having a
handle; <as>as, a <ex>handled</ex> magnifying glass is easier to
use</as>. Opposite of <ant>handleless</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-handled</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: -handled
<hw>-handled</hw> <pos>suff.</pos> <def>having a usually specified type
of handle; <as>as, a pearl-<ex>handled</ex> revolver; a
long-<ex>handled</ex> shovel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>handleless</ent>⟦br⟧
